
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-chen-ntps-ra-opt-00.txt'>
    <title>"The IPv6 Router Advertisement Option for NTP Configuration", Xu Chen, Dacheng Zhang</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-chen-ntps-ra-opt-00.txt</link>
    <description>This document defines a new ND option, called the NTPS option, that contains the Server location information of Network Time Protocol version 4[draft-ntpv4] or greater. Therefore, hosts can get such information in the same RA message transporting the information of IP address configuration. In this spec, both ND transport mechanisms (i.e., advertisements and solicitations) are considered.</description>
    <dc:date>2010-02-25T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
